811	% ============================================================
812	\section{Conclusion}
813	\label{sec:conclusion}
814	
815	Every agent interaction produces a next-state signal that encodes how the agent performed and, often, how it should have acted differently.
816	\method{} is built on a single insight: these signals are stream-agnostic, and one policy can learn from all of them simultaneously.
817	Personal conversations, terminal executions, GUI interactions, SWE tasks, and tool-call traces all flow into the same training loop.
818	Binary RL converts evaluative signals into scalar process rewards, while OPD converts directive signals into token-level advantage supervision. Combining the two yields significant optimization gains.
819	The result is a system where a model simultaneously personalizes to individual users and improves at long-horizon agentic tasks, trained entirely from the interactions it is already having. 
